# x402 Auction MCP Project Rules

## Code Style
- Follow KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid) principles
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions small and focused
- Use descriptive names
- Avoid unnecessary complexity

## Architecture
- `index.ts` - MCP server routing only
- `handlers.ts` - Business logic and validation
- `api.ts` - HTTP communication only
- `types.ts` - Type definitions
- `constants.ts` - Configuration values

## Adding New Features
1. Add constants to `constants.ts`
2. Add types to `types.ts`
3. Add API function to `api.ts`
4. Add handler to `handlers.ts`
5. Add tool and route to `index.ts`

## Testing Changes
```bash
npm run build
node build/index.js  # Should print "x402 Auction MCP Server running on stdio"
```

## Principles
- Single Responsibility: Each file has ONE job
- Open/Closed: Easy to extend, hard to break
- Simple error handling: Consistent patterns
- No deep nesting: Keep it flat

